Question: What is a relationship deal breaker for you?
Answer:
Lately it has become a huge importance in any friendship/ relationship. But I find one of the main important aspects in a relationship or friendship would be communication or compromise. Your significant other or friends should be able to know and understand what your going through or how you may feel/ be affected etc. Without communication and understanding theres a lot of misunderstandings and conflict which can break trust/ cause a breakup to happen.
  
  Sit down and talk to those people and tell them how you are feeling, make sure they understand or reassure you both got it and will work together to fix whatever issue it may be. Also if there's zero communication then it's mainly one person who is working hard to maintain those friendships and relationships which results in a lot of emotional days and hard feelings, which can just become a very toxic and negative place you're in so it's best to just let go of that person and move on.

Answer: Some random pictures from the last month or so.... This is what life has been looking like. I havenâ€™t really been posting much lately cause Iâ€™ve just been thinking a lot. I know this year was not what anyone expected and everyoneâ€™s plans went into the trash so it might be hard to make any plans or think about how this year could be, but regardless of how crazy things get around us, there are still things that we can control. Our behaviors, mindsets, how we treat ourselves and those around us, our habits... Itâ€™s easy to feel like thereâ€™s no point in changing or growing when your future feels so uncertain, but actually the future is always uncertain. Weâ€™re just more aware of that fact right now. Iâ€™ve been thinking about how I view people and the world and how I can change that to a more positive view while still being realistic lol, dealing with some anxiety-inducing mindsets that Iâ€™ve gotten so used to experiencing but am realizing theyâ€™re actually something I can change, thinking about how I want relationships with family and friends to be better and what type of conversations I need to have or effort I need to put in to do that, thinking about what effect I have had on the world and what effect God wants me to have on the world and how I can better serve Him in the work that I do, thinking about the lifestyle I live and how I want to have a healthier more organized one while still having time to relax and have balance in my life. I encourage you to think about these things for yourself and how you can grow this year regardless of how things go.
